Running a business as an introverted creative who is very private should not be complicated, yet it sometimes is. Most online resources and coaches tell you to work with the big (and devilish) technology companies using extroverted techniques. Do advertising here, follow the algorithm, share who you are. Have your service checked, be available 24/7, answer questions with a video of yourself, respond immediately. Video, video, video.
01/03/2024
This is a year of transition for me.
I do not want to feed my money, my data, and my energy to the big technology companies. Nor do I want coaches who have only one extroverted solution they apply to everyone. I am exploring new ways to manage my business while fighting against the idea I have long believed in, that you have to do things a certain way to be successful.
Wish me luck!
I have already taken the first steps.
I left FB, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and deleted my private WhatsApp account.
I also removed the last external tracker, Google Analytics, from my website yesterday, and it feels good.
I recently subscribed to a CRM based in Europe for better GDPR compliance, and I will be transferring my business over the next few weeks.
I transferred my MX to Proton and am now fully benefiting from SPF, DKIM, and DMAR, without having to pay Google for basic email address validation.
03/03/2024
